The paper focuses on Natural Language Generation (NLG) for open-domain question answering (QA) using statistical models and large datasets. This falls under the sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) which deals with natural language processing and understanding. The paper also uses machine learning techniques such as multi-task learning and encoder-decoder frameworks, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) research. Additionally, the paper deals with knowledge graphs and ontologies, which are relevant to Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Database (cs.DB) research.
